    <string name="provider_image_help_title">Image understanding guide</string>
    <string name="provider_image_help_estimated_title">Why is one result \"estimated\"?</string>
    <string name="provider_image_help_estimated_body">Estimated means AstrBot judged support from the provider type and model name. It is fast, but it can be wrong if the model alias is unusual or the provider changed behavior.</string>
    <string name="provider_image_help_tested_title">Why can the tested result fail?</string>
    <string name="provider_image_help_tested_body">Tested sends a small real image request to the model. Failure usually means the API key, endpoint, model permissions, or the model\'s actual image support is not ready.</string>
    <string name="provider_image_help_fallback_title">Which models fit image caption fallback?</string>
    <string name="provider_image_help_fallback_body">Use a chat model that can really read images, such as Gemini vision-capable models, OpenAI-compatible vision models, or Ollama models with vision/VL in the name. That model can caption images for text-only chat models.</string>
